{
  "texts": [
    "For the authors who reached this threshold, the total co-citation strength was determined, as illustrated in Figure 4.",
    "Figure 4 depicts nodes that represent references, with the size of the node indicating the cumulative number of citations that have referenced the given citation.",
    "A co-citation relationship is symbolised by a link connecting two nodes, with the thickness of the link indicating the number of citations associated with the reference.Subsequently, it was deemed necessary to analyse the links between authors and co-authors to identify the prominent research groups operating within a specific field.",
    "The accomplishment was attained by the process of delineating the connections between the authors and co-authors, as illustrated in Figure 5.",
    "The mapping process provides a visual representation of the relationship, which makes it easier to study not only the activity of an author but, the interconnectivity with other research groups as well."
  ]
}